    <item>
      <title>Phase 1: The Local Automator — OS Mastery for DevOps Engineers</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/python/phase1/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 19 Apr 2026 08:00:00 +0530</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/python/phase1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Phase 1: The Local Automator (Week 4–6)&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;phase-1-the-local-automator-week-46&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#phase-1-the-local-automator-week-46&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal:&lt;/strong&gt; Master the local Operating System layer before touching the cloud.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Every line below is explained in plain English so a beginner can follow along.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What You Will Learn&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;what-you-will-learn&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-you-will-learn&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Module&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;What it does&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;os&lt;/code&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;code&gt;pathlib&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Move files, check directories, read secret keys from the OS&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;subprocess&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Run any terminal command (&lt;code&gt;git&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;kubectl&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;docker&lt;/code&gt;) from inside Python&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;json&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Convert Python data ↔ JSON files — the language every API speaks&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;logging&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Write timestamped records of every action (the professional alternative to &lt;code&gt;print()&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Module 1 — &lt;code&gt;os&lt;/code&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;code&gt;pathlib&lt;/code&gt;: File and Directory Control&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;module-1--os--pathlib-file-and-directory-control&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#module-1--os--pathlib-file-and-directory-control&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Why you need this&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;why-you-need-this&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#why-you-need-this&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every automation script needs to check folders, read secret keys, and create files.&#xA;&lt;code&gt;os&lt;/code&gt; gives you raw access to the operating system.&#xA;&lt;code&gt;pathlib&lt;/code&gt; makes file paths safe and readable on Windows, Mac, and Linux simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
